'''Kokushi Daijiten''' (国史大辞典) is a [[historical dictionary]] of [[Japanese history]] published by [[Yoshikawa Kōbunkan]] during the [[Meiji era]] and [[Shōwa era]] in two separate editions.

* For the first Japanese historical dictionary compiled by {{ill|Kuniharu Yashiro|ja|八代国治|12=draft|12=draft}} and others in [[1908]], see '''{{ill|Kokushi Daijiten (Meiji era)|ja|国史大辞典 (明治時代)|12=draft|12=draft}}'''.
* For the largest Japanese historical dictionary compiled by {{ill|Tarō Sakamoto (historian)|ja|坂本太郎 (歴史学者)|12=draft|12=draft}} and others between [[1979]] and [[1997]], see '''{{ill|Kokushi Daijiten (Shōwa era)|ja|国史大辞典 (昭和時代)|12=draft|12=draft}}'''.

{{Ambiguous}}








