'''Kokushi Daijiten''' (国史大辞典) is a [[historical dictionary]] of [[Japanese history]] published by [[Yoshikawa Kōbunkan]] during the [[Meiji era]] and [[Shōwa era]] in two separate editions.
* For the first Japanese historical dictionary compiled by {{ill|Kuniharu Yashiro|ja|八代国治|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuniharu Yashiro|qq=}} and others in [[1908]], see '''{{ill|Kokushi Daijiten (Meiji era)|ja|国史大辞典 (明治時代)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kokushi Daijiten (Meiji era)|qq=}}'''. * For the largest Japanese historical dictionary compiled by {{ill|Tarō Sakamoto (historian)|ja|坂本太郎 (歴史学者)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tarō Sakamoto (historian)|qq=}} and others between [[1979]] and [[1997]], see '''[[:en:Kokushi Daijiten|Kokushi Daijiten (Shōwa era)]]'''.
